Detailed Description

Queue is an abstract class/interface.

There are three types: Stack(): A Last In First Out Queue. FIFOQueue(): A First In First Out Queue. PriorityQueue(lt): Queue where items are sorted by lt, (default <). Each type supports the following methods and functions: q.append(item) -- add an item to the queue q.extend(items) -- equivalent to: for item in items: q.append(item) q.pop() -- return the top item from the queue len(q) -- number of items in q (also q.__len()) Note that isinstance(Stack(), Queue) is false, because we implement stacks as lists. If Python ever gets interfaces, Queue will be an interface.
